  "prompt": "Are maps of New York City free?",
  "response": "Yes, many maps of New York City are available for free. You can find several resources to obtain maps, including:\n\n1. **NYC Official Website**: The New York City government website often offers downloadable maps of the city.\n  \n2. **Visitor Centers**: Tourist information centers around the city provide free printed maps that highlight attractions, neighborhoods, and transportation options.\n\n3. **Mobile Apps**: Various smartphone apps, such as Google Maps, offer free navigation and mapping services for NYC.\n\n4. **Libraries**: Public libraries in NYC, such as the New York Public Library, may have free maps available for visitors.\n\n5. **Online Resources**: Websites like Yelp, TripAdvisor, and others often provide downloadable or printable maps of the city.\n\nKeep in mind that while many resources are free, some specialized maps (like detailed transit maps or specific neighborhood guides) might have a cost associated with them.",
